HB 664 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session LaCombe
Abstract: Increases the maximum fine imposed for violations of parish ordinances from
$500 to $1,500.
Present law provides that the maximum penalty that may be imposed for the violation of a
parish ordinance is a $500 fine and imprisonment of 30 days in the parish jail.
Proposed law provides for an increase of the maximum fine that may be imposed for the
violation of a parish ordinance from $500 to $1,500.
Present law provides that the maximum penalty that may be imposed for violation of any
parish ordinance as codified in Title 11 or 13 of the Code of Ordinances for the parish of
East Baton Rouge and the city of Baton Rouge is $1,000 and imprisonment of six months
in the parish jail.
Proposed law provides for an increase of the maximum fine that may be imposed for the
violation of a parish ordinance in East Baton Rouge and the city of Baton Rouge from
$1,000 to $1,500.
