Present law provides that in Jefferson Parish, except as to properties zoned or used for
industrial activities, the maximum penalty which may be imposed for violation of any parish
ordinance is $1,000 and imprisonment of six months in the parish jail.
Proposed law provides for an increase of the maximum fine that may be imposed for
violation of any parish ordinance in Jefferson Parish from $1,000 to $1,500.
Proposed law otherwise retains present law.
(Amends R.S. 33:1243(A)(1) and (2) and (B)(1))
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The House Floor Amendments to the engrossed bill:
1. Increase the maximum fine which may be imposed for violation of any parish
ordinance as codified in Title 11 or 13 of the Code of Ordinance for the parish
of East Baton Rouge and the city of Baton Rouge from $1,000 to $1,500.
2. Increase the maximum fine which may be imposed for violation of any parish
ordinance in Jefferson Parish from $1,000 to $1,500.
